result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Filed: Original Transcript of Preliminary Hearing ( 16 pages) commencing 09-29-2022 by Valerie Richter.

Defendant Charice Anntoinette Evans appeared by video.  Attorney Katherine Graber appeared by video for Charice Anntoinette Evans.  Attorney Katherine Seelow appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: SD. 
Pretrial Conference held.  Defense counsel still needs offer and additional time to review discovery with defendant.  Case adjourned, Br. 41.
Pre-trial conference scheduled for November 14, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Charice Anntoinette Evans appeared by video.  Attorney Katherine Graber appeared by video for Charice Anntoinette Evans.  Attorney Katherine Seelow appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: SD. Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: Adrianna LaMack, Milwaukee Police Department Officer.  State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 41.
Pre-trial conference scheduled for October 18, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Charice Anntoinette Evans in court.  Attorney Katherine Graber in court for Charice Anntoinette Evans.  Attorney Katherine Seelow in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Case set for a preliminary hearing. State's witness is unavailable for today's proceedings and requests an adjournment. Defense moves to dismiss. Court GRANTS the State's request for an adjournment. Court finds CAUSE to adjourn the preliminary. Defendant waived time limits for Preliminary Hearing. Case is adjourned to Br. 41.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for September 29, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant waived time limits for Preliminary Hearing.

Defendant Charice Anntoinette Evans in court with attorney Katherine Graber. Gerald Henry Alder on behalf of Katherine Seelow appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case in court for order to show cause hearing. Defense counsel has been appointed to the case. Court schedules case for preliminary hearing. Case adjourned to Branch 35. Parties are advised that effective August 1, 2022 this case will be assigned to Judge Audrey Skwierawski, Branch 41 in Room 501 of the Courthouse.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for September 2, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Charice Anntoinette Evans in court.  Katherine Seelow appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case in court for preliminary hearing. OPD needs additional time to appoint an attorney. Court holds colloquy with the defendant. Court adjourns case for an attorney to be appointed. Court orders a respresentative from the SPD appear on the next date if an attorney is not appointed. Court finds good CAUSE to adjourn preliminary hearing. Case adjourned to Branch 35.  Order to show cause hearing scheduled for July 15, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Charice Anntoinette Evans in court.  Katherine Seelow appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case in court for preliminary hearing. OPD needs additional time to appoint an attorney. Court holds colloquy with the defendant. Court adjourns case for an attorney to be appointed. Court finds good CAUSE to adjourn preliminary hearing. Case adjourned to Branch 35 VIA ZOOM.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 10, 2022 at 08:30 am.

DEFENDANT WAS ORDERED BY THE COURT TO REPORT TO THE MILWAUKEE COUNTY JAIL (CJF) TO BE BOOKED AND RELEASED BY 5:00 P.M. ON (4-08-2022). IF THEY FAIL TO APPEAR A BENCH WARRANT WILL BE ISSUED FOR THEIR ARREST.
Court orders defendant to comply with all family court orders in place.

Defendant Charice Anntoinette Evans in court with attorney Vincent Paul Guimont.  Sara Beth Hill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Rosa, Branch 35.
Defendant given a copy of complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT MAY QUALIFY FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Case is adjourned for preliminary hearing in Branch 35.
Court ordered arrest warrant withdrawn.  Recall issued.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for April 27, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Arrest Warrant received from the D.A.'s office on filing date of Criminal Complaint.
